So far, you've learned about the many ways to test your Chef code and speed up the feedback loop. Now, go deeper by learning more about proven techniques for writing elegant tests.

In the articles and videos that follow, you'll learn more about:

* refactoring a cookbook test suite to make sure the tests are clear, concise and fast.
* what unit and integration tests are and how they apply to the domain of cookbook development.
* how to eliminate redundancy, rebuild common patterns into helpers, and build portable libraries.
* using Test Kitchen to create safe environments to try out new ideas.
